# HOW TO USE
# for production, create `.env.production` and update these values (npm run production will use .env.production)
# for staging, create `.env.staging` and update these values (npm run staging will use .env.staging)
# for development, create `.env.development` and update these values (npm run dev will use .env.development)
# for test, create `.env.test` and updates these values (npm run test will use .env.test)
# all .env.* files (except for .env.sample) are in .gitignore to avoid accidental commits to git

